<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Argfeld</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-02 13:41:01</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have saved up 6000 pp to buy one of these bags.  When I checked the price at the gnome, he wanted 5980 pp for it.  I then went and killed a bunch of kobolds and (with permission) "tagged" a bunch of other kobolds that others were killing for the faction.  After about an hour of this,  the gnome wanted 5760 pp and had gone from dubious to apprehensive.  Anyhow, what I am getting at is that faction has a major impact on the price of this bag and is not that hard to adjust.  Also, I have seen the price of this bag fluctuate slightly (by maybe 10 pp) even when I have killed nothing to affect the faction or altered my charisma.</font></td></tr></table>
